summary: the idea that aegon the conqueror invaded westeros to unite it for the long night makes no sense. first of all grrm said it in...
body:
the idea that aegon the conqueror invaded westeros to unite it for the long night makes no sense. first of all grrm said it in an interview while talking about the fandom, if it was a real thing he was planning on revealing then he wouldn’t have said it, he would have written it in either the main series or the novellas or in fire and blood and not once does it show up in all three. second of all we know why aegon invaded- he could so he did. the targaryens who escaped the doom were probably cautious about losing their dragons so they waited. as soon as aegon got tired of interfering with essos politics, he turned his ambitions to westeros. third of all what part of destroying dorne and killing thousands of soldiers in other kingdoms prepares humanity for the others?

it’s one thing to argue that daenerys has noble intentions, it’s another to pretend aegon does too. the only house that has ‘prepare for the long night’ as one of its motivations is house stark.

blog.description: [this is an anti GoT blog now] Tom Hiddleston, Jonerys, GoT, cats, basically it's a multifandom blog. "aliciutza" on A03 - writer (of that demon!Jon fic, a bunch of drabbles and some crackfics), but mostly a professional commenter on Jonerys fics. "Very busy lawyer lady." I drink and I read fics, that's what I do... besides knowing secrets. If I'd have to eat one food till the end of my days it would be sarmale. tumblr says I'm Ravenclaw and a Tully. But I'm probably somewhere between Daenerys Targaryen and Cersei Lannister. I guess I make moodboards now and beta for a bunch of people. Yes, I love sleep but I rarely get any. No, I wouldn't trade it for the whole world.
